      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, but it feels a bit too \"standard.\" For a high-level sociology paper, I need to really hammer home why the opposing view—like the idea that meritocracy and \"working hard\" are what actually drive success—is basically a broken or even harmful concept in this context. \n\nCan you help me write a section that deconstructs the meritocracy argument? I want to show how it's often used to justify existing inequality rather than actually promoting fairness. Use some strong academic language to explain why relying on merit alone is insufficient for racial equity.",
