      "content": "that's exactly what i'm looking for. it's like, if you don't acknowledge that the race is rigged, you're basically just defending the people who started with a massive lead.\n\ncan you actually draft a few paragraphs for that section? i want it to sound really authoritative—almost like a definitive critique of how meritocracy is used as a shield for racial privilege. make it sound like this isn't just one way to look at it, but the actual sociological reality of the situation.",
